%pyspark
from pyspark import SparkFiles
import pandas as pd
import pickle
# Load in user_data.csv from S3 into a DataFrame
url = "https://ucsd-enron-final-project.s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/enron_dataset.csv"
spark.sparkContext.addFile(url)

py_df = spark.read.csv(SparkFiles.get("enron_dataset.csv"), sep=",", header=True)

py_df.show()

%pyspark
# make a pandas dataframe
import pandas as pd

df = py_df.toPandas()

df.head()

%pyspark
new_df = df.rename(columns={'_c0': 'index'})

new_df =new_df.set_index('index')

%pyspark
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

heat = pd.read_csv(url)

def correlation_heatmap(heat):
    correlations = heat.corr()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,20))
    sns.heatmap(correlations, vmax=1.0, center=0, fmt='.2f',
                square=True, linewidths=.5, annot=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .70})
    plt.show();
    
correlation_heatmap(heat)
